António Guterres, Secretary-General of the United Nations, has called for an end to the attack on peaceful protesters in Nigeria. His call follows Tuesday's massacre of young Nigerians protesting against police brutality across the country by thugs and security agents. The UNSG Antonio Guterres
unmissions He said the UN was ready to help Nigeria find a solution that will swiftly de-escalate the situation. See Also






